   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the purpose
     of providing a classification of an attribute on an EXPRESS entity. 
     The standard values used by the classification are defined as
     <express_ref linkend="class:arm:Class_arm.Class">
       Classes
     </express_ref>.
   </p>
   <note number="1">
     The definition of the 
     <express_ref linkend="class:arm:Class_arm.Class"/>
     may be stored in an external class library.
   </note>
   <note number="2">
     When the attribute of an EXPRESS entity is classified, the value of
     the attribute on an instance of the EXPRESS entity will be the 
     <express_ref linkend="class:arm:Class_arm.Class.name">name</express_ref>
     or 
     <express_ref linkend="class:arm:Class_arm.Class.id">identifier</express_ref>
     of the class.
   </note>
 </purpose>
 <inscope>
   <li>
     the association of a value, represented by a class, to an attribute on
     an entity.
     <note>
       the entities are defined by other modules that extend this module.
     </note>
   </li>
 </inscope>

 <outscope>
   <li>
     the existence of a class.
   </li>
 </outscope>

